# Day 15 Scratch &mdash; Conditionals

First, let's explore the ninth lesson in the unit. To begin, find your ECS Version 5 curriculum and open to page 164-165.

[Access a Digital Copy of the lesson>>](http://code.org/ecs#page=164)

## Key Concepts

- Students will be introduced to conditionals, using the "if" block and "or" block, and how to use them to enhance a variable program.

## Common Difficulties

The difference between if and else can be confusing for students. In addition creating the conditions for conditionals is probably the trickiest thing for students. Using real world examples and demoing the thought process of creating conditionals will likely be helpful to students.

Students will need files: [age.sb](http://www.exploringcs.org/curriculum), [age solution.sb](http://www.exploringcs.org/curriculum), [age-greater-equal.sb](http://www.exploringcs.org/curriculum).

